my town, because it

00:27:37.120 --> 00:27:39.480
was a town where they were
just a wonderful group

00:27:39.480 --> 00:27:44.110
of supportive parents, my
parents and music teachers.

00:27:44.110 --> 00:27:47.420
And when I was in sixth
grade, I was writing songs.

00:27:47.420 --> 00:27:51.140
I was given an assignment
to write a short story

00:27:51.140 --> 00:27:53.590
about the book "Jonathan
Livingston Seagull."

00:27:53.590 --> 00:27:56.509
And being the Libra creative
person that I am, I said,

00:27:56.509 --> 00:27:58.550
instead of writing a short
story, I wrote a song.

00:27:58.550 --> 00:27:59.720
And I showed the
teacher the song.

00:27:59.720 --> 00:28:00.910
You said, well, that's
a really good song.

00:28:00.910 --> 00:28:03.634
She said, why don't we teach
this to all the sixth graders?

00:28:03.634 --> 00:28:05.550
And so she taught it to
all the sixth graders,

00:28:05.550 --> 00:28:07.091
and it was performed
in a sixth grade

00:28:07.091 --> 00:28:09.470
assembly for all the kids.

00:28:09.470 --> 00:28:11.070
And then later on
in high school,

00:28:11.070 --> 00:28:12.350
I continued writing songs.

00:28:12.350 --> 00:28:14.058
And one of my best
friends in high school

00:28:14.058 --> 00:28:17.140
was murdered by her boyfriend--
Donyale Morton, may she ever

00:28:17.140 --> 00:28:17.930
rest in peace.

00:28:17.930 --> 00:28:22.570
And after she passed, I
needed to do something

00:28:22.570 --> 00:28:24.930
to process my feelings.

00:28:24.930 --> 00:28:26.780
And I wrote a song
called "Always Be There."

00:28:26.780 --> 00:28:28.670
And once again, I showed
it to some of the teachers

00:28:28.670 --> 00:28:29.253
at the school.

00:28:29.253 --> 00:28:31.370
And they were very
moved by the song.

00:28:31.370 --> 00:28:33.810
And I shared it
with her parents.

00:28:33.810 --> 00:28:36.450
And then one of the teachers
was a dance choreographer

00:28:36.450 --> 00:28:37.660
at the school, Ms. Miller.

00:28:37.660 --> 00:28:40.240
And she said, I'm going
to choreograph something

00:28:40.240 --> 00:28:41.960
to this song so that
this will forever

00:28:41.960 --> 00:28:45.379
live in the Teaneck
Terpsichoreans repertoire.

00:28:45.379 --> 00:28:46.670
So she choreographed something.

00:28:46.670 --> 00:28:47.890
And then other
students came forward.

00:28:47.890 --> 00:28:49.764
We'll do a poem, and
then we'll do something.

00:28:49.764 --> 00:28:52.380
So the birth of that song
created a whole evening

00:28:52.380 --> 00:28:54.640
where 2,000 people
came to just give

00:28:54.640 --> 00:28:57.400
